Plan: Dynamic Response Body Allocation                                                                                                
Context                                                                                                                               
HttpResponse.body is a fixed char body[65536] array baked into the struct.
Every response is silently capped at 64 KB — large directory listings, big file.
downloads, and large text files either truncate or hit the "file too large" guard.
The fix: make the body heap-allocated and growable so there is no hard cap. 

